          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599138718566-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Once everything has softened, add most of your <strong>curry powder</strong> (save a little for garnish!) and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599138724270-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599138724270-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599138724270-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599138724270-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599138724270-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> tomato ketchup </strong>and<strong> </strong>200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has reduced to a thick gravy-like consistency – this is your<strong> curried tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Once thickened, remove the pan from the heat and set aside</p><p>Warm through again just before serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599138737782-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599138737782-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599138737782-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599138737782-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599138737782-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to your <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>kale</strong> and massage it with clean hands so that it's evenly covered in oil</p><p>Once the sausages are cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and sprinkle over the <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 3-4 min or until the kale is cooked and slightly crispy – this is your <strong>sausage</strong> <strong>tray bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1599138747158-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1599138747158-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
